## Dev commands

```bash
flutter pub get
scripts/codegen.sh
flutter run -d linux
scripts/ci_checks.sh
```

## Forbidden

- Direct HTTP from widgets/providers bypassing client layer
- Hand-editing generated Dart files
- Hardcoded user-facing strings (use slang `t.*`)
- Breaking Drift migrations without `schemaVersion` bump + migration strategy
- Platform-specific playback paths without `Platform.is*` guards
- Glass on media cards, posters, or video surface (`liquid-glass-ui.mdc`)
- Committing with failing CI checks (use `SKIP_HOOKS=1` only when user explicitly bypasses)
